title: The Smartest Investors Are Buying These 3 Beaten-Down Stocks
description: Instead, his core strategy is to buy quality stocks at reasonable valuations -- and his holdings include positions in the first two companies discussed here.  Apple (NASDAQ: AAPL), UPS (NYSE: UPS), and Alphabet (NASDAQ: GOOG) (NASDAQ: GOOGL) all face earnings headwinds in 2023, but they will likely emerge stronger from any recession that coult potentially kick off this year.  A combination of supply chain disruptions, a weakening environment for consumer discretionary spending, and adverse foreign currency exchange movements hit Apple in calendar 2022, and some of those issues are likely to extend well into 2023.

title: The post-pandemic corporate profit boom in America really is over: ‘More margin pressure ahead’
description: Profit margins are shrinking, squeezed by inflation and an economic outlook that’s eroded the ability to pass on costs by raising prices.

title: AI plans from Microsoft, Google spur more interest across tech sector
description: Market interest in artificial intelligence technology remained high this week, with Google taking much of the spotlight.
